



Sir
Camp two miles from Pages. April 24th 1781. 7 oClock at night.



I have this moment arrived at this placeand shall loose no time. I beg to recieve your orders as I am Ignorant of the Situation of Richmond. I would write more explicitly but for prudential Reasons of which your Excellency will easily Concieve. I am most respectfully Yr Excellencys most obt. Sert.,

Jas Innes


P.S. I hope to hear from you by the Dawn of Day.

